With Christmas around the corner, you may be wondering what to get the reader in your life. Book lovers are notoriously difficult to shop for. Besides books, there are other items to bring a smile to the face of that special reader in your life. Scented Candle If there is one thing a true reader enjoys, it’s the smell of books. These days things have gone digital; every true book lover remembers and enjoys the scent of the pages book. This scented candle will replicate the nostalgic scent of an old book store. The candle is handmade with 100% pure natural eco soy wax in London. The Old Bookshop Soy Wax Scented Candle Made with natural ingredients and essential oils and burns for 40 hours. Personalised Book Every book lover dreams of one day having a story told about them. This is a very personal gift that will be treasured for years to come. Tell a story of a special occasion and it will be on the top shelf of every reader’s bookshelf. Book Light There’s nothing worse than disappearing into a good book and having to stop because the light isn’t good. If you want to save your favorite bookworm’s eyes, get them the Really Tiny Book Light. This little gadget is small, portable, and clips onto any book. It allows the reader to read anytime and anywhere. Get it from Exclusive Books Scribd Subscription The digital age is upon us. Gift the special person in your life a subscription to an online book service. Scribd has millions of ebooks, audiobooks, magazines, and more. It’s the perfect gift for the reader who doesn’t have time to sit and read. The platform features many famous books in audio format. Available for Apple and Android platforms. We all need to start taking control of our finances by budgeting, investing and building… In February 2019, Thandi Ntuli was invited to headline at an artist curated, artist led… As the days get warmer and Spring reveals newness all around, discovering something new to… 